Niger State Command of Nigeria Immigration Service(NIS) has explained that it has registered more than 6,000 regular and irregular migrants under the migrants’ e-registration exercise in the state. Comptroller of Immigration Service in charge of the state’s command of the service, Alhaji Mamman Ango stated this while fielding questions from journalists in Minna the state’s command headquarters of the service. ALSO READ: Inordinate ambition of national chairman responsible for Edo APC crisis ―  Edo speaker Niger governor signs 2020 Appropriation Bill into law Dabiri-Erewa seeks multi-agency approach to end human… Buhari condoles with Niger over terrorist attack I supplied AK-47 to bandits in Niger, Katsina, Zamfara,… The NIS Boss, who spoke through the image-maker of the service, Malam Abubakar Mukhtar said the migrants so far captured were those from Africa, Asia and Europe. According to him, some foreign nationals from neighbouring states of Kwara and Kogi were captured in the state due to what they described as congestion in those states. He, however, described the exercise as a huge success, adding that though the amnesty period had elapsed, they were now waiting for further directives from the service’s headquarters in Abuja, for further action. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.